cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving response selection for multi-turn human-computer conversation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with retrieval modeling, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of neural networks and ensemble models suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
